Troubleshooting
LiME compilation fails: Ensure kernel headers match your running kernel version

uname -r
dpkg -l | grep linux-headers
Wine issues with DumpIt: Configure Wine properly

winecfg
# Set Windows version to Windows 10
Volatility analysis errors: Verify memory dump format and file integrity

file linux_memory.lime
vol3 -f linux_memory.lime linux.check
Conclusion
You have successfully completed volatile memory acquisition using both DumpIt for Windows environments and LiME for Linux systems. This lab demonstrated critical digital forensics skills including memory dump creation, analysis techniques, and artifact extraction. These capabilities are essential for incident response, malware analysis, and forensic investigations where volatile memory contains crucial evidence that would be lost upon system shutdown.

The hands-on experience with both tools provides practical knowledge for real-world forensic scenarios where memory acquisition is time-critical and requires reliable, proven methodologies.
